                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Do you have a full HR department? If the company is big enough, I would say start by getting out of the middle. Let HR take over.. Give them the full story, both sides in all honesty but try to get them to keep you anonymous. I think that if it came to court you would probably lose the anonymity and have to testify. I think no matter how you play it you'll regret the choices in the long run unless you are completely honest. Call it like you saw it.
<br />

<br />
If you surround yourself with the truth in this (especially if you get HR involved) you should have no worries for your own job. You'd probably, in fact, be more secure than you were before.
<br />

<br />
