                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">She should definately talk to the HR department.
<br />

<br />
The fact that she got the things (probably) because the boss was 'friendly' with her does make it hard to sympathize with her, however she still has the legal right to say 'NO' at any time. If the boss doesn't honor that, and continues with this kind of behavior, that leaves him open to losing his job and a lawsuit. And if the *company* doesn't do anything about the boss making a hostile work environment for her *they* leave themselves open to a lawsuit.
<br />

<br />
If she's uncomfortable telling the boss to back off she can still talk to HR.
<br />

<br />
And it doesn't have to be a boss making it a hostile environment. A coworker, or even a vendor (delivery boy) can do so and if the boss/company don't take steps to correct it they are open to legal action.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Max
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=368646" target="_blank" class="postlink">Fanamax the Enchanter</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
