                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">harrassment doesn't have to be sexual in nature to still be considered harrassment.  Legally it is considered harrassment when someone who is in a position of power over you treats you in a manner that is unacceptable in your company's rules and procedures for dealing with employees.
<br />

<br />
Yes, she may have "asked" for it and "enjoyed" it at the beginning when she was liking the perks until he got out of hand.. but it is still a case of harrassment and illegal in the workplace.  
<br />

<br />
I would definitely get out of the middle in this situation.. it is a very bad place to be.. and all those who told you to go to the HR Department is right.. if your company is too small to have an HR Dept.. then go to your supervisor.. if you are not comfortable with that then go to your supervisor's boss.. you gotta start someplace... just tell what you know. .and ask to be kept out of it... Not sure you can.. but you can try.. especially since techincally she is your assistant.
<br />

<br />
good luck to you.. that is not a great situation to be in.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Salinu Stormbringer
